00:22:04.690 --> 00:22:10.980
which we assume points
along the z-axis.

00:22:10.980 --> 00:22:13.410
And then, of
course, we know that

00:22:13.410 --> 00:22:16.530
from our previous
discussion that the spin

00:22:16.530 --> 00:22:18.420
undergoes precession.

00:22:18.420 --> 00:22:23.130
It's sort of precesses
around the magnetic field

00:22:23.130 --> 00:22:24.140
at the Larmor frequency.

00:22:27.700 --> 00:22:46.070
And now, let's assume we
have-- the yellow shows up.

00:22:46.070 --> 00:22:48.570
We have a rotating field.

00:22:48.570 --> 00:22:52.580
We add a rotating
field eight B1,

00:22:52.580 --> 00:22:55.550
and just to keep
things simple, we

00:22:55.550 --> 00:23:00.330
want to assume that the
rotating field rotates

00:23:00.330 --> 00:23:03.280
at the same frequency
as a magnetic moment,

00:23:03.280 --> 00:23:06.310
so we are on a resonance.

00:23:06.310 --> 00:23:13.430
Because what happens
now is we can simply

00:23:13.430 --> 00:23:16.690
do a transformation
to the rotating frame.

00:23:19.920 --> 00:23:26.390
The rotating frame is now
at the Larmor frequency

00:23:26.390 --> 00:23:31.730
and we have just learned that in
the rotating frame, of course,

00:23:31.730 --> 00:23:38.120
in the rotating frame the
rotating field stands still,

00:23:38.120 --> 00:23:43.190
so it becomes a
static field which

00:23:43.190 --> 00:23:45.705
points in the x direction.

00:23:52.850 --> 00:23:58.620
And we have the static
field in the z direction,

00:23:58.620 --> 00:24:01.280
but now that's what
I just reviewed.

00:24:01.280 --> 00:24:06.840
We have a fictitious
magnetic field,

00:24:06.840 --> 00:24:09.560
which comes from the
transformation to the rotating

00:24:09.560 --> 00:24:14.290
frame and on resonance,
at the Larmor frequency,

00:24:14.290 --> 00:24:17.085
this is exactly the
negative of B naught.

00:24:20.660 --> 00:24:27.660
So in other words,
we started out

00:24:27.660 --> 00:24:33.160
to expose a magnetic moment
to a time-dependent field.

00:24:38.810 --> 00:24:54.010
So we had a rotating field
cosine omega Lt sine omega Lt.

00:24:58.460 --> 00:25:04.790
But in the rotating frame,
this becomes now the x prime x,

00:25:04.790 --> 00:25:06.800
and it's stationary
in the rotating frame.

00:25:10.940 --> 00:25:15.360
So this was the field
in the lab frame.

00:25:15.360 --> 00:25:31.770
In the rotating frame, we
have an effective field,

00:25:31.770 --> 00:25:34.590
which is the field
in the lab frame

00:25:34.590 --> 00:25:40.850
minus the fictitious field,
and the fictitious field

00:25:40.850 --> 00:25:42.240
was given by that.

00:25:42.240 --> 00:25:45.750
It just cancels the
B naught component.

00:25:45.750 --> 00:25:51.150
And in the rotating frame,
this vector and this vector

00:25:51.150 --> 00:25:55.250
cancels and we are just left
with a field of strengths

00:25:55.250 --> 00:26:03.930
B1, which points in
the x-axis, or actually

00:26:03.930 --> 00:26:08.410
the x-axis in the rotating
frame is what I call x prime.

00:26:08.410 --> 00:26:11.240
So therefore, we have
a very simple problem

00:26:11.240 --> 00:26:13.140
that in the rotating frame.

00:26:13.140 --> 00:26:18.200
We have a static
field of value B1.

00:26:22.839 --> 00:26:24.630
And the good thing is,
we know already what

00:26:24.630 --> 00:26:28.240
a magnetic moment does
with a static field.

00:26:28.240 --> 00:26:30.140
The magnetic moment
is just precessing

00:26:30.140 --> 00:26:33.190
around the static
magnetic field.

00:26:33.190 --> 00:26:35.850
So therefore, our
solution is now

00:26:35.850 --> 00:26:39.020
we have transformed the
time-dependent field

00:26:39.020 --> 00:26:53.040
and now we know that mu
precesses around this field,

00:26:53.040 --> 00:26:57.240
and the precession frequency
is the Rabi frequency, which

00:26:57.240 --> 00:26:58.970
we discussed previously.

00:27:04.700 --> 00:27:10.310
The Rabi frequency is the
gyromagnetic ratio times B1.

00:27:10.310 --> 00:27:13.080
So therefore, if
we would start out

00:27:13.080 --> 00:27:19.670
with a magnetic moment
aligned with the z-axis.

00:27:19.670 --> 00:27:25.200
If we would wait
half a Rabi's cycle,

00:27:25.200 --> 00:27:28.885
the magnetic moment
would now be inverted.

00:27:32.440 --> 00:27:34.800
So the situation is we have
a magnetic moment which

00:27:34.800 --> 00:27:38.010
points in the z-axis with
a field in the z-axis.

00:27:38.010 --> 00:27:41.440
But we expose it
to a rotating field

00:27:41.440 --> 00:27:43.270
which rotates in the xy plane.

00:27:47.080 --> 00:27:50.240
So in the rotating frame,
we have a stationary field

00:27:50.240 --> 00:27:52.970
which points in x.

00:27:52.970 --> 00:27:56.010
In this rotating frame,
the spin is simply

00:27:56.010 --> 00:28:00.030
precessing around what
is now a steady field,

00:28:00.030 --> 00:28:04.550
and after half a Ravi
cycle, the spin points down.

00:28:04.550 --> 00:28:07.680
So therefore we know--
going back to lab frame--

00:28:07.680 --> 00:28:12.660
that this rotating field has
caused in quantum mechanics

00:28:12.660 --> 00:28:15.770
I would say a spin
flip, a full reversal

00:28:15.770 --> 00:28:19.290
of the magnetic
moment, and this is

00:28:19.290 --> 00:28:23.750
what we call the pi
pulse-- it has already

00:28:23.750 --> 00:28:29.810
rotated the spin by pi--
or we call it a spin flip,

00:28:29.810 --> 00:28:32.030
but it's a completely
classical system.

00:28:37.760 --> 00:28:38.480
Any questions?

00:28:48.430 --> 00:28:51.660
Well, then I would
question for you.

00:28:51.660 --> 00:28:58.180
I've discussed with you the case
that the rotating field rotates

00:28:58.180 --> 00:29:01.660
at the Larmor frequency.

00:29:01.660 --> 00:29:13.530
But now I want to discuss the
case that the rotating field is

00:29:13.530 --> 00:29:16.680
not at the Larmor
