00:29:59.040 --> 00:30:02.350
And I want you to think
about it for a moment

00:30:02.350 --> 00:30:05.870
and then decide if
we go off resonant,

00:30:05.870 --> 00:30:08.660
if we drive this system
away from the resonance

00:30:08.660 --> 00:30:11.320
with a rotating field which
is faster than the Larmor

00:30:11.320 --> 00:30:18.260
frequency, what is
now the oscillation

00:30:18.260 --> 00:30:23.575
frequency of the
magnetic moment.

00:30:31.940 --> 00:30:44.860
And so the choices are, is it
larger, smaller, or the same?

00:30:44.860 --> 00:30:51.560
And this was, of course,
compared to the Rabi frequency.

00:30:58.780 --> 00:31:03.860
So I've explained to you
that the spin flip, the Rabi

00:31:03.860 --> 00:31:07.000
flopping, or the pi
pulse-- and this picture

00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:12.520
was at the magnetic moment--
does Rabi flopping rotates

00:31:12.520 --> 00:31:18.260
plus z minus, z plus, z minus,
z at the Rabi frequency.

00:31:18.260 --> 00:31:20.930
But now we drive
the system faster

00:31:20.930 --> 00:31:23.230
than the Larmor frequency
and the question

00:31:23.230 --> 00:31:26.410
is, is whatever this
magnetic moment does,

00:31:26.410 --> 00:31:28.657
is it faster, slower,
or does it always

00:31:28.657 --> 00:31:29.865
happen at the Rabi frequency?

00:31:43.070 --> 00:31:45.220
Larger.

00:31:45.220 --> 00:31:45.720
Good.

00:31:48.910 --> 00:31:53.630
Well, let me then immediately
add another twist.

00:31:53.630 --> 00:31:56.890
What would happen-- let's
