00:32:51.340 --> 00:32:52.190
OK, good.

00:32:52.190 --> 00:32:56.320
So that means I can go very
quickly about the explanation.

00:32:56.320 --> 00:32:57.210
It's correct.

00:32:57.210 --> 00:33:00.450
Whenever you are off
resonant, this system

00:33:00.450 --> 00:33:04.970
precesses faster,
so let me summarize

00:33:04.970 --> 00:33:08.420
what probably is
obvious to all of you.

00:33:08.420 --> 00:33:13.110
What happens when we have an
off-resonant rotating field.

00:33:17.940 --> 00:33:20.870
When we have an
off-resonant rotating field,

00:33:20.870 --> 00:33:25.370
we go to the rotating frame, but
of course, the rotating frame

00:33:25.370 --> 00:33:29.420
we go to is now not rotating
at the Larmor frequency

00:33:29.420 --> 00:33:31.620
because the purpose of
going to rotating frame

00:33:31.620 --> 00:33:33.860
is get rid of the time
dependence of the rotating

00:33:33.860 --> 00:33:34.540
field.

00:33:34.540 --> 00:33:37.070
So we go to rotating
frame which rotates

00:33:37.070 --> 00:33:40.820
at the frequency of
the rotating field.

00:33:40.820 --> 00:33:56.515
So if the rotating field
rotates at a frequency omega,

00:33:56.515 --> 00:34:01.210
we have a fictitious field,
which is omega over gamma.

00:34:01.210 --> 00:34:02.715
Gamma is the gyromagnetic ratio.

00:34:06.570 --> 00:34:11.750
For the resonant case, we
were just completely canceling

00:34:11.750 --> 00:34:14.030
the static field
in the z direction,

00:34:14.030 --> 00:34:16.750
but for the
off-resonant case, when

00:34:16.750 --> 00:34:21.480
omega is larger or
smaller in both cases,

00:34:21.480 --> 00:34:26.690
this one here is no longer 0.

00:34:26.690 --> 00:34:33.139
And our total
effective field is now

00:34:33.139 --> 00:34:42.630
the quadrature sum of what
we have in the z direction,

00:34:42.630 --> 00:34:46.360
and what we have in the x
direction or x prime direction,

00:34:46.360 --> 00:34:46.889
this is B1.

00:34:49.780 --> 00:34:54.429
So in the z direction,
we have the static field

00:34:54.429 --> 00:35:02.960
minus the fictitious field
and then the two are added up

00:35:02.960 --> 00:35:06.320
On resonance, the angle
theta is 90 degrees,

00:35:06.320 --> 00:35:09.480
but for the off-resonant
case, the angle

00:35:09.480 --> 00:35:18.720
is different given by the
simple geometric result.

00:35:18.720 --> 00:35:28.910
And the effective field is the
quadrature sum of B1 squared

00:35:28.910 --> 00:35:50.120
plus B naught
minus-- and the fact

00:35:50.120 --> 00:35:54.270
is this adds something to the
effective field in the rotating

00:35:54.270 --> 00:35:57.490
frame whether we drive it
above or below resonance.

00:35:57.490 --> 00:36:10.070
So therefore the
magnetic moment precesses

00:36:10.070 --> 00:36:18.500
at what is called
the generalized Rabi

00:36:18.500 --> 00:36:34.200
frequency, which I now call--
this would be red-- let's use

00:36:34.200 --> 00:36:41.420
green instead-- the generalized
Rabi frequency, which

00:36:41.420 --> 00:36:50.620
is gamma times B
effective, and this

00:36:50.620 --> 00:36:59.830
is the quadrature
sum of the detuning

00:36:59.830 --> 00:37:07.310
plus the capital
letter omega, omega R,

00:37:07.310 --> 00:37:10.120
is the Rabi frequency
at resonance,

00:37:10.120 --> 00:37:13.440
and this is nothing else
than a measure for the drive

00:37:13.440 --> 00:37:17.130
field for the strengths of the
drive field B1 in frequencies.

00:37:19.640 --> 00:37:22.820
So therefore, the
generalized Rabi frequency

00:37:22.820 --> 00:37:27.110
is the resonant Rabi
frequency added in quadrature

00:37:27.110 --> 00:37:28.330
with the detuning squared.

00:37:40.460 --> 00:37:41.515
Any questions?

00:37:47.770 --> 00:37:55.140
So because it's an exact result
and I like the result Rabi

00:37:55.140 --> 00:37:58.140
flopping at the
generalized Rabi frequency,

00:37:58.140 --> 00:38:01.160
I want to derive it for you.

00:38:01.160 --> 00:38:06.430
So I want to figure out what
is the dynamic of a spin which

00:38:06.430 --> 00:38:13.400
is originally
aligned, and now it

00:38:13.400 --> 00:38:18.830
undergoes-- it is driven
by the rotating field.

00:38:18.830 --> 00:38:21.770
Remember, the resonant
case was very simple.

00:38:21.770 --> 00:38:24.160
The spin was just
doing Rabi flopping.

00:38:24.160 --> 00:38:27.540
It was fully inverted,
came back, and just

00:38:27.540 --> 00:38:30.980
did this at that Rabi frequency.

00:38:30.980 --> 00:38:33.880
Now we know that in
the off-resonant case,

00:38:33.880 --> 00:38:36.690
there will be an
effective magnetic field

00:38:36.690 --> 00:38:39.740
and it will precess at a
faster frequency, which

00:38:39.740 --> 00:38:46.620
is a generalized
Rabi frequency, but

00:38:46.620 --> 00:38:51.940
since the effective magnetic
field is not transverse,

00:38:51.940 --> 00:38:59.440
it has a z component, the
spin will never fully invert.

00:38:59.440 --> 00:39:02.180
So geometrically,
it's very easy.

00:39:02.180 --> 00:39:06.820
We start out with a magnetic
moment at zero time,

00:39:06.820 --> 00:39:10.530
and I can immediately draw
to you the complete solution.

00:39:10.530 --> 00:39:18.710
The complete solution is that
in the rotating frame, this sort

00:39:18.710 --> 00:39:26.130
of precesses around the
effective magnetic field.

