00:53:18.220 --> 00:53:21.800
And this aspect
of classical spins

00:53:21.800 --> 00:53:24.720
is called rapid
adiabatic passage.

00:53:46.080 --> 00:53:50.340
So we want to add one more
piece to our discussion.

00:53:50.340 --> 00:53:55.360
So far we have assumed a static
field and a rotating field,

00:53:55.360 --> 00:53:58.040
which rotates at one frequency.

00:53:58.040 --> 00:54:01.240
But now we want to change
the frequency of the rotating

00:54:01.240 --> 00:54:02.280
field.

00:54:02.280 --> 00:54:06.300
So we have our magnetic moment
in a static magnetic field,

00:54:06.300 --> 00:54:08.380
which is our quantization axis.

00:54:08.380 --> 00:54:10.260
And now we have
a rotating field,

00:54:10.260 --> 00:54:13.640
but we increase the frequency
of the rotating field from slow

00:54:13.640 --> 00:54:16.670
to fast and ask what happens.

00:54:16.670 --> 00:54:20.460
And the result is that by
increasing the frequency,

00:54:20.460 --> 00:54:23.230
sweeping the frequency
through the resonance,

00:54:23.230 --> 00:54:25.510
we can do something very useful.

00:54:25.510 --> 00:54:27.890
We can invert the spin.

00:54:27.890 --> 00:54:32.220
We can turn over the magnetic
moment in a very robust way,

00:54:32.220 --> 00:54:35.550
and this is the concept of
rapid adiabatic passage.

00:54:35.550 --> 00:54:38.550
A lot of you may be
familiar with the concept

00:54:38.550 --> 00:54:40.920
a Landau-Zener
transition, what I'm

00:54:40.920 --> 00:54:44.790
telling you what is exactly
the classical counterpart

00:54:44.790 --> 00:54:46.700
of the Landau-Zener transition.

00:54:46.700 --> 00:54:49.770
actually in many cases when
it comes to spin physics,

00:54:49.770 --> 00:54:53.030
the classical physics and the
quantum physics is the same.

00:54:53.030 --> 00:54:56.430
So that's why I want to
discuss rapid adiabatic passage

00:54:56.430 --> 00:55:03.970
and Landau-Zener physics first
in the classical environment.

00:55:03.970 --> 00:55:09.610
So rapid adiabatic
passage is a technique

00:55:09.610 --> 00:55:20.800
for inverting turning around
spins or magnetic moments

00:55:20.800 --> 00:55:28.550
by sweeping the frequency
of your drive field

00:55:28.550 --> 00:55:29.980
across the resonance.

00:55:36.160 --> 00:55:48.875
So adiabatic means that this
frequency sweep has to be slow.

00:55:53.800 --> 00:55:59.905
Slow is slow compared
to the Larmor frequency.

00:56:04.810 --> 00:56:08.080
We get any given moment the
magnetic moment precesses

00:56:08.080 --> 00:56:14.360
at the Larmor frequency, which
is the gyromagnetic ratio

00:56:14.360 --> 00:56:17.030
times g-factor
magnetic field, so it's

00:56:17.030 --> 00:56:18.970
sort of quasi stationary.

00:56:18.970 --> 00:56:22.450
The spin precesses around
the effective magnetic field

00:56:22.450 --> 00:56:25.700
and we want to change the
frequency of the drive

00:56:25.700 --> 00:56:29.820
slow compared to that motion.

00:56:29.820 --> 00:56:31.940
Well, the word rapid
adiabatic passage

00:56:31.940 --> 00:56:35.890
has the word adiabatic, which
means slow but also rapid.

00:56:41.140 --> 00:56:44.270
The word rapid means
we have to be rapid

00:56:44.270 --> 00:56:47.540
compared to relaxation
processes, which we do not

00:56:47.540 --> 00:56:50.860
discuss here in an
idealized environment.

00:56:50.860 --> 00:56:53.030
For instance, if you do
rapid adiabatic passage

00:56:53.030 --> 00:56:55.950
in the environment where
the atoms can collide,

00:56:55.950 --> 00:56:59.570
rapid means you have to do it
fast enough before you have

00:56:59.570 --> 00:57:04.400
decoherence in two collisions,
so slow compared to the Larmor

00:57:04.400 --> 00:57:08.370
frequency and rapid
compared to all the things

00:57:08.370 --> 00:57:12.900
I'm not mentioning
here-- rapid compared

00:57:12.900 --> 00:57:17.270
to decoherence and
relaxation processes.

00:57:31.910 --> 00:57:38.940
I will not set up differential
equation and solve them.

00:57:38.940 --> 00:57:47.120
I want to give you the intuitive
picture of what goes on,

00:57:47.120 --> 00:57:53.330
but then also
derive what is sort

00:57:53.330 --> 00:57:56.329
of the criterion
for adiabadicity,

00:57:56.329 --> 00:57:57.370
which we have to fulfill.

00:58:07.270 --> 00:58:08.630
So what are our ingredients?

00:58:08.630 --> 00:58:11.450
We have a magnetic moment, mu.

00:58:15.300 --> 00:58:18.310
We have a static field B naught.

00:58:20.920 --> 00:58:32.750
We have a drive field B1, which
rotates at a frequency omega.

00:58:32.750 --> 00:58:41.930
And we assume that
the rotating field

00:58:41.930 --> 00:58:45.310
is smaller than
the static field.

00:58:45.310 --> 00:58:48.220
It's not absolutely
necessary, but you

00:58:48.220 --> 00:58:50.060
apply a big static
field and then you

00:58:50.060 --> 00:58:51.210
